 of government requirements for the fiscal year 1925 Mr Coolidge declared against the bonus for which he said there was no sound reason The President said the government had no funds to distribute to any rlass of its citizens that it does not take from the pockets of all of the people Compensation he said should be limited to the war incapacitated and wounded 400000000 Surplus The estimates provide for total ex penditures of 3298080444 in the fiscal year This would leave a sur plus of almost 400000000 but the projected reduction in tax rates would take away more than threequarters of the expected surplus which was cal culated on ithe basis of present tax levies The tax reduction proposal offered by Mr Coolidge follows the lines sug gested by Secretary Mellon in a recent letter to Acting Chairman Green of"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-22T16:19:13.070Z", "group": ["ndnp/whi", "wisconsin-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85040613/1923-12-19/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_dynamite_ver01:data:sn85040613:00514151301:1923121901:0351/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=504&w=337", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_dynamite_ver01:data:sn85040613:00514151301:1923121901:0351/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1009&w=675", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_dynamite_ver01/data/sn85040613/00514151301/1923121901/0351.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "wisconsin", "eagle river", "vilas"], "location_city": ["eagle river"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["vilas"], "location_state": ["wisconsin"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["1", "3", "sn85040613", "0", "5", "0000000002", "4"